The description of the lesions and the application of 5% acetic acid solution turning the lesions white suggests HPV infection, specifically with types 6 and 11, which are known to cause genital warts. Neisseria gonorrhoeae typically presents with urethritis, cervicitis, or proctitis, while HSV type 2 causes painful, vesicular lesions.
